 The Complete Flow: From User Input to Execution

  1. User Types Macro Delimiter:

  "Please analyze this MVR using [MVR Peer Review]"

  2. System Detects Macro:

  # Regex pattern finds: [MVR Peer Review]  
  # Extracts: "MVR Peer Review"
  # Checks registry: ✅ Found

  3. Macro Triggers Progressive Complexity:

  🔧 Detected macro: MVR Peer Review
  📊 Select complexity level:
     🟢 Simple (2-5 min): Basic compliance check
     🟡 Enhanced (10-20 min): Evidence-focused review
     🔴 Advanced (20-45 min): AI-powered comprehensive

  4. Behind-the-Scenes: TidyLLM Pipeline Executes:

  # User never sees this - it's the implementation
  result = (mvr_document
      |> filter(document_type="mvr")
      |> select("filename", "content", "sections")
      |> mutate(section_analysis=analyze_sections_sequentially)
      |> invoke_persona("MVR Validation Expert")
      |> reshape("compliance_matrix")
  )

  5. User Sees Human-Readable Progress:

  🔄 Parsing Table of Contents to section level 1.1.1.1
  ✅ Found 89 sections in MVR document
  🔄 Extracting model context (Credit Risk Model, Tier 1)
  ✅ Model context extracted successfully
  🔄 Performing section-by-section analysis with evidence tracing
  ✅ Analyzed all sections, mapped conclusions to evidence
  🔄 Generating peer review challenges and confidence scores
  ✅ Generated 12 peer challenges, confidence scores calculated
  🔄 Creating detailed compliance matrix
  ✅ Compliance matrix generated with 89 rows

  📊 Results: 85% compliance, 3 areas need attention

  🎯 The Key Point You Made

  The macro delimiters [MVR Peer Review] are what the user types - they're not pipe syntax. The
   pipes (|>) are the internal implementation that users never see.

  User Experience:
  - Types: [MVR Peer Review]
  - Gets: Human-readable progress and results

  System Implementation:
  - Detects: [MVR Peer Review] bracket pattern
  - Executes: |> filter |> select |> mutate pipeline internally
  - Shows: Progress messages and final results

  The users get powerful workflows through simple [bracket 
  syntax] without needing to know the complex tidyverse implementation underneath.
